Forts.: 31 Decbr 66.
Many thanks for your last the Lord be praised to have spared you suterday.
I am glad you see His hand in all those things.

You say nothing of your health I hope that it is better. I send you a fla-
nell through David you might put it at night round your stomach.

I with you for this next year many blessings. God knows well what we want
we have to pray and recieve with gratitud that which He gives us.

The time is short. we have to look for our Lords coming

My love to all our dear people
